radiographic_examinations.findings: Inflamed blind-ending tubular structure in the right lower quadrant measuring approximately 11 mm in diameter with evidence of hyperdense material consistent with appendicoliths. No evidence of free air or drainable fluid collection. Visualized lung bases are clear. Normal visualized heart without pericardial effusion. Normal liver, gallbladder, bilateral adrenal glands, spleen, pancreas, and bilateral kidneys. No bowel obstruction. Normal aorta. No free fluid or free air throughout the abdomen. No mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy. Normal bladder, prostate, rectum, and sigmoid colon.
